commit.message:
Added example notebook and helper function to calculate phik matrix with spark

- Updated spark instructions in README

Two speedups of the phik code

- phik value of each variable-pair is calculated in parallel
- code to calculate phik is twice as fast, number of scipy.stats.mvn.mvnun
  evaluations has been reduced with factor of two. Thanks to symmety.
- Precision of brentq optimization has been slightly reduced.
- Bump up version to 0.9.11, turn off test requirements in setup.py
- Remove unused imports
- Also allow large number of bins in phik calculation.

commit.message:
Bump up version to 0.9.9

- in bivariate.py, added bivariate_normal_theory distribution
  patch for entry levels that are below machine precision
  (simulation does not work otherwise)
- parallelize the simulation datasets
- ignore notebook test warning
- update of readme.rst, include global_phik() example.
added dq checks to global correlation and array functions
update version to 0.9.7
update documentation to include data quality
fixed problem with UF OF bins and missing bins in outlier calculation
added more protection against data quality issues
small fix in binning and added functionality to detect non clean data

Update to version 0.9.6

The correlation_report() function now has new option store_each_plot,
which allows one to store each plot in an individual file.

The function returns an additional dict with the location of each stored file.

Update to version 0.9.5

Update all required package version to those installed
in a clean conda python v3.6 environment.
Update to version 0.9.4

Remove trailing space in '% matplotlib inline' in notebooks

Not accepted by all jupyter versions.
Update to version 0.9.3

Turned off numba forceobj=True option in simulation.py

Turns out it made phik really slow.
